; Regression test for issue #761: Make uncommoditized amounts behave like commoditized ones (BZ#761)
; https://github.com/ledger/ledger/issues/761
;
; When dividing amounts, commoditized amounts respect the commodity's display
; precision (e.g., $10/3 = $3.33 rounded to 2 decimal places), while
; uncommoditized (plain number) amounts show excessive precision (10/3 = 3.333333).
; The issue requested uncommoditized amounts behave like commoditized ones.

2024/01/01 Commoditized
    Assets:Commoditized    $10.00
    Income:Source          $-10.00

2024/01/01 Uncommoditized
    Assets:Plain    10
    Income:Other    -10

test reg Assets:Commoditized --amount "amount / 3"
24-Jan-01 Commoditized          Assets:Commoditized           $3.33        $3.33
end test

test reg Assets:Plain --amount "amount / 3"
24-Jan-01 Uncommoditized        Assets:Plain               3.333333     3.333333
end test
